column2: Overall, how often do you use the internet?
column3: Do you do use social media?
column4: Does social media make you feel more connected to information about what's going on in your friends' lives?
column5: Does social media make you feel worse about your own life because of what you see from other friends on social media?
column6: Does social media make you feel better connected to your friends' feelings?
column7: Does social media make you feel pressure to post content that will be popular and get lots of comments or likes?
column8: Does social media make you feel pressure to only post content that makes you look good to others?
column9: Do you ever experience on social media people posting about things you werent invited to?
column10: Do you ever experience on social media people stirring up drama?
column11: Do you ever experience on social media people posting things about you that you cant change or control?
column12: Do you ever experience on social media people supporting you through challenges or tough times?
column13: People get to show different sides of themselves on social media that they cant show offline
column14: People are less authentic and real on social media than they are offline?
column15: People share too much information about themselves on social media?
column16: Was there anyone in the room who watched or helped you take the survey?
